<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Type: Cartesian_transformation
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.cartesian_transformation">
The <b>cartesian_transformation</b> type is a mechanism to refer to an instance of either a 2d or 3d cartesian transformation operator.
 </ext_description>
 
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Type: Geometric_mapping_target
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.geometric_mapping_target">
The <b>geometric_mapping_target</b> type is a mechanism to refer to an instance of <b>Axis_placement</b>, of <b>Cartesian_transformation_2d</b> or of <b>Cartesian_transformation_3d</b>. 
 </ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Type: Template_instance
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.template_instance">
The <b>template_instance</b> type is a mechanism to refer to an instance of <b>Mapping_based_template_instance</b> or of <b>Transformation_based_template_instance</b>. 
 </ext_description>
 
 
  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Geometric_coordinate_space 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space">
A <b>Geometric_coordinate_space</b> is a type of <b>Numerical_representation_context</b> that defines a coordinate space where geometric elements can be defined. It is either two-dimensional or three-dimensional. 
<p>
There shall be at least two units specified for the <b>Geometric_coordinate_space</b>: one length unit and one plane angle unit.
</p> 
<p>
The length unit applies to each coordinate direction.
</p>
 <example>
The length unit millimeter and the angle unit radian are examples of units that may assigned to a <b>Geometric_coordinate_space</b>. 
 </example>
    
 <note>
The origin for coordinate values is implicitly defined as being the cartesian point whose coordinates are all zero.
 </note>
 </ext_description>

 <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Geometric_coordinate_space Attribute: dimension_count
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space.dimension_count">
the dimensionality of the geometric space.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Geometric_coordinate_space Where: WR1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space.wr:WR1">
the dimensionality shall be greater than zero.
</ext_description>

 <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Detailed_geometric_model_element 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element">
A <b>Detailed_geometric_model_element</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:foundation_representation_arm.representation_item">Representation_item</express_ref>.
It identifies a geometric construct.
<note>
The Detailed_geometric_model_element needs to be specialized in the application modules that use the present application module.
</note>
   </ext_description>

	   <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Detailed_geometric_model_element Where:IP1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element.wr:IP1">
A Detailed_geometric_model_element shall be an item of a Geometric_model or serves to create an item of a Geometric_model.
   </ext_description>

 <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Detailed_geometric_model_element Where:IP2
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element.wr:IP2">
The instances of Geometric_model that contain the Detailed_geometric_model_element shall all have the same dimension_count
   </ext_description>	 

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Geometric_model 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model">
A Geometric_model is a type of <b>Representation</b> dedicated to the description of geometric constructs.
<p>The <b>Geometric_model</b> is founded in a <b>Geometric_coordinate_space</b>.
</p>
<p>
The items of Geometric_model are instances of <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element">Detailed_geometric_model_element</express_ref>.
</p>
   </ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Geometric_model  Attribute: is_defined_in 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model.SELF\Representation.context_of_items">
The <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space">Geometric_coordinate_space
</express_ref> in which the <b>Geometric_model</b> is defined.  
    </ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Geometric_model  Attribute: version_id 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model.version_id">
The version_id specifies the version identifier of the <b>Geometric_model</b>. 
    </ext_description>


  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Geometric_model  Attribute: SELF\Representation.items 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model.SELF\Representation.items">
The instances of Detailed_geometric_model_element that are included in the <b>Geometric_model</b>.  
    </ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Geometric_model  Attribute: model_extent 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model.model_extent">
The model_extent specifies the radius of a sphere that encloses all elements of the geometric model.
The centre of the sphere is located at the origin of the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space">
Geometric_coordinate_space</express_ref> of the <b>Geometric_model</b>. 
 <p>The model_extent need not be specified for a particular <b>Geometric_model</b>.
 </p> 
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_point
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point">
A <b>Cartesian_point</b> is a type of <b>Detailed_geometric_model_element</b> that defines a point by a list of up to 3 cartesian coordinates.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_point Attribute: coordinates
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point.coordinates">
The list of up to 3 length measure values that define the cartesian coordinates of the point.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Direction
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Direction">
A <b>Direction</b> is a type of <b>Detailed_geometric_model_element</b> that defines a 2 or 3 dimensional vector.
<note number="1">A Direction is not located in a geometric space but is used in the definition of geometric entities like axis_placements.
</note>
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Direction Attribute: coordinates
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Direction.coordinates">
The list of 2 or 3 length measure values that define the direction ratios of the direction.
<note number="2">The coordinates of a Direction may not be normalised and the actual magnitudes
of the components have no effect upon the direction being defined: only the ratios x:y:z or x:y are
significant.
</note>
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement">
An <b>Axis_placement</b> is a type of <b>Detailed_geometric_model_element</b> that defines a right-handed, 2D or 3D, coordinate system.
<p>
If the <b>Axis_placement</b> belongs to a 3D geometric space, the third direction of the coordinate system is defined by the vector product of x_axis and y_axis.
</p>
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement Attribute: origin
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.origin">
The <b>Cartesian_point</b> that defines the position of the Axis_placement in the geometric space.
</ext_description>
	  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement Attribute: x_axis
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.x_axis">
The <b>Direction</b> that defines the first axis of the Axis_placement.
</ext_description>	
	  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement Attribute: y_axis
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.y_axis">
The <b>Direction</b> that defines the second axis of the Axis_placement.
</ext_description>
	  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement Derive: dim
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.dim">
The dimensionality of the Axis_placement. It is equal to the number of coordinates of the origin.
</ext_description>
	  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement WHERE: WR1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.wr:WR1">
The dimensionality of the Axis_placement shall be greater than 1.
</ext_description>
	  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement WHERE: WR2
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.wr:WR2">
The number of coordinates of the x_axis shall be equal to the number of coordinates of the origin of the Axis_placement.
</ext_description>		

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement WHERE: WR3
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.wr:WR3">
The number of coordinates of the y_axis shall be equal to the number of coordinates of the origin of the Axis_placement.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement WHERE: IP1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.wr:IP1">
The vector product of x_axis and y_axis shall not be result in a null vector.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_transformation_2d
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_2d">
A <b>Cartesian_transformation_2d</b> is a geometric transformation defined in a 2D geometric space by a 2*2 matrix and a cartesian point.
<p>Let be:</p>
<ul>
<li>MM, the 2*2 multiplication matrix of the cartesian transformation</li>
<li>A, the point of the cartesian transformation</li>
<li>P, a point in the geometric space</li>
<li>Q, the result of the application of the transformation to P</li>
</ul>
<p>The coordinates of Q shall be obtained by the formula: Q = MM*P + A</p>
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_transformation_2d Attribute: multiplication_matrix
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_2d.multiplication_matrix">
The array of two instances of Direction that defines the multiplication matrix of the transformation.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_transformation_2d Attribute: translation
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_2d.translation">
The <b>Cartesian_point</b> that defines the position of the Axis_placement in the geometric space.
</ext_description>

	  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_transformation_2d WHERE: WR1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_2d.wr:WR1">
The first element of the matrix shall refer to a 2-dimensional Direction.
</ext_description>
	  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_transformation_2d WHERE: WR2
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_2d.wr:WR2">
The second element of the matrix shall refer to a 3-dimensional Direction.
</ext_description>		

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_transformation_2d WHERE: WR3
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_2d.wr:WR3">
The translation point shall have 2 coordinates.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_transformation_3d
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_3d">
A <b>Cartesian_transformation_3d</b> is a geometric transformation defined in a 3D geometric space by a 3*3 matrix and a cartesian point.
<p>Let be:</p>
<ul>
<li>MM, the 3*3 multiplication matrix of the cartesian transformation</li>
<li>A, the point of the cartesian transformation</li>
<li>P, a point in the geometric space</li>
<li>Q, the result of the application of the transformation to P</li>
</ul>
<p>The coordinates of Q shall be obtained by the formula: Q = MM*P + A</p>

</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_transformation_3d Attribute: multiplication_matrix
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_3d.multiplication_matrix">
The array of three instances of Direction that defines the multiplication matrix of the transformation.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_transformation_3d Attribute: translation
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_3d.translation">
The <b>Cartesian_point</b> that defines the position of the Axis_placement in the geometric space.
</ext_description>

	  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_transformation_3d WHERE: WR1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_3d.wr:WR1">
The first element of the matrix shall refer to a 3-dimensional Direction.
</ext_description>
	  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_transformation_3d WHERE: WR2
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_3d.wr:WR2">
The second element of the matrix shall refer to a 3-dimensional Direction.
</ext_description>		

	  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_transformation_3d WHERE: WR3
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_3d.wr:WR3">
The third element of the matrix shall refer to a 3-dimensional Direction.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Cartesian_transformation_3d WHERE: WR4
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_3d.wr:WR4">
The translation point shall have 3 coordinates.
</ext_description>

		
  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement_mapping 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement_mapping">
An <b>Axis_placement_mapping</b> is a geometric transformation defined by a source <b>Axis_placement</b> and a target <b>Axis_placement</b> that results from the transformation of the source one.
<p>Both instances of <b>Axis_placement</b> shall have the same dimensionality.</p>
<p>The transformation shall be computed as the isometric transformation that maps:</p>
<ul>
<li>the origin of the source onto the origin of the target;</li>
<li>the x_axis of the source onto the x_axis of the target;</li>
<li>the y_axis of the source onto the y_axis of the target.</li>
</ul>
<note>by construction, the determinant of the transformation matrix equals one.</note>
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement_mapping Attribute: source
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement_mapping.source">
The <b>Axis_placement</b> that plays the role of source in the transformation.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement_mapping Attribute: target
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement_mapping.target">
The <b>Axis_placement</b> that plays the role of target in the transformation.
</ext_description>

	  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement_mapping WHERE: WR1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement_mapping.wr:WR1">
The source and the target shall have the same dimensionality.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement_transformation_mapping 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement_transformation_mapping">
An <b>Axis_placement_transformation_mapping</b> is a geometric transformation defined by a source <b>Axis_placement</b> and a target <b>Cartesian_transformation</b>.
<p>The transformation shall be computed as the transformation that maps:</p>
<ul>
<li>the origin of the source onto the translation point of the target;</li>
<li>the x_axis of the source onto the first element of the multiplication_matrix of the target;</li>
<li>the y_axis of the source onto the second element of the multiplication_matrix of the target.</li>
<li>in case the transformation is a 3D transformation, the normalised vector product of the x_axis and the y_axis of the source onto the third element of the multiplication_matrix of the target.</li>
</ul>
<note>This kind of mapping enables to represent non isometric transformations, including symmetry and projection transformations.</note>
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement_transformation_mapping Attribute: source
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement_transformation_mapping.source">
The <b>Axis_placement</b> that plays the role of source in the transformation.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement_transformation_mapping Attribute: target
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement_transformation_mapping.target">
The <b>Cartesian_transformation</b> that plays the role of target in the transformation.
</ext_description>

	  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Axis_placement_transformation_mapping WHERE: WR1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement_transformation_mapping.wr:WR1">
The source and the target shall have the same dimensionality.
</ext_description>
		

